text: <!channel> All-call! I’m looking for blog contributors for the month of November. If you’re interested in writing a post, please reach out to me. And don’t worry if you don’t have as much experience with blogging/don’t know what to write about. I can help brainstorm ideas and put together outlines for posts. Would love everyone’s voice to be heard.

text: <@U06DFL7BP|charlesv> pinned a message to this channel.

Also, here is a bit more context: 
We are focusing the posts on topics related to our pillars: heart, people, momentum, patterns and hunger. These pillars won’t be public facing but the post should relate to one of these themes in a way. For example, Leia just wrote a post on the Node Summit, which I thought fit well under hunger. And Marissa is writing a post about the Hour of Code volunteering and I feel like that will fit well under heart.

The topic can be around anything you want: something in response to current design/tech news, an opinion piece, a DIY project, something educational, something about culture, etc.

For reference, we are looking for blog posts to be around 350-500 words for SEO purposes but they can be longer if need be. (Not shorter).
